## Third-Party Data Sources

FishON! Lite fetches **public data** from government APIs to show river and tide conditions. These services may have their own privacy policies:

### Data Sources We Use

1. **USGS Water Services API**
   - URL: https://waterservices.usgs.gov/
   - Purpose: Real-time river flow data
   - Privacy: Public data, no user information sent
   
2. **Bureau of Reclamation**
   - URL: https://www.usbr.gov/
   - Purpose: Additional river monitoring data
   - Privacy: Public data, no user information sent
   
3. **NOAA CO-OPS API (Tides and Currents)**
   - URL: https://tidesandcurrents.noaa.gov/
   - Purpose: Real-time tide and current data
   - Privacy: Public data, no user information sent
   
4. **National Weather Service API**
   - URL: https://weather.gov/
   - Purpose: Weather conditions at river/tide locations
   - Privacy: Public data, no user information sent

**Important:** When you use the app, we send requests to these APIs to fetch data. These requests contain:
- The specific gauge or station ID you're viewing
- Your general location (state/region) to filter available gauges

**We do NOT send:**
- Your device ID
- Your precise GPS location
- Any personal identifying information

